Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Software Engineer, MyPay* role with *Chime*. I bring over three years of professional experience building production-grade backend systems at scale, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered backend services where correctness, resiliency, and performance are non-negotiable — exactly the technical depth the MyPay role demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I designed and built a distributed, high-scale backend service exposing 1,000+ API endpoints, enforcing strict input validation and idempotent tool execution to guarantee correctness and resiliency under concurrent load. To coordinate complex workflows across microservices, I architected a concurrent multi-agent orchestration system using LangChain and LangGraph, enabling reliable real-time execution and measurable scalability improvements. I also drove rapid iteration and experimentation cycles through generative code solutions — API-aware templates, SDK patterns, and code-generation workflows — and optimized prompt routing and agent concurrency to reduce end-to-end latency by 60% and LLM API costs by 50%, demonstrating a strong product mindset and bias toward measuring impact. Prior to Sperse, at Qualitest, I designed a cloud-agnostic backend service in Python backed by PostgreSQL (transactional database) and Redis (caching) for financial-grade file operations across Google Cloud Storage, S3, and MinIO via expiring signed URLs. I also contributed to an Identity & Access Management platform built with React, Spring Boot, and AWS supporting thousands of users across 30+ applications — requiring high-scale API design, cross-functional collaboration, and rigorous reliability standards — and developed backend workflows using AWS Step Functions to orchestrate long-running data import jobs, ensuring end-to-end pipeline resiliency. Together, these roles have prepared me to independently own and deliver features end-to-end, proactively identify opportunities for improving reliability and scalability, and collaborate effectively across engineering, product, and data teams.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in systems-level thinking and technical communication — skills that translate directly into the engineering discipline and Team First culture Chime values. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I conducted applied research on StyleGAN and Stable Diffusion using CUDA, PyTorch, and LoRA on Pace University's HPC cluster, managing the full model development lifecycle from training to inference optimization via vLLM and Hugging Face deployment. Beyond building the systems myself, I led workshops on GPU programming and AI Agent development for 50+ students — designing and delivering those sessions required me to break down complex technical concepts clearly and accessibly, mirroring the collaborative, knowledge-sharing culture that makes cross-functional teams thrive.

I have always been passionate about making everyday banking helpful, easy, and free for the people who need it most, and I am excited by the opportunity to contribute to Chime's mission of helping members achieve financial peace of mind. MyPay's role as Chime's fastest-growing, revenue-driving product — powering real-time money movement at scale for everyday Americans — is exactly the kind of high-impact, technically demanding work I want to be doing. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

